ning shot of this movie.\nHow its silhouette is language enough.\n\nWe know it for what it is.\n\nCities we have heard of while\nliving in another.\n\n\nAnd in each city - landmarks and hand marks.\n\nHand codes, longhands, hobo signs.\n\nA dump, a dive, a joint.\nA venue, vistas and avenues.\nOne way streets, dire straights,  neighbourhoods we only lived in briefly.\n\nSanctuaries.\n\n\nagainst all odds encounters.\n\n\nSometimes it is worth adressing the city directly.\n\nBurning a match or incense \nplaying a song in an empty room\nto an open window.\n\n\nA whisper:\n\ninto the night\nTo go home safely.\n\n\nAt a café : don't delay my lover.\n\n\nin a park : you are made of trees too\n\nPopulation : ∞\n"
